Build Gate Proviso:
- Never render or expose spreadsheet letter identifiers in generated content or public-facing pages.
- Always use semantic entity names (for example, `Intervention Dominance`, `Coverage Timing`, `Evidence Type`).
- Treat any letter-identifier wording in generated outputs as a validation failure that must be fixed before build.

When creating or editing Primary Mechanism (PM) pages:

Follow:
- `system/primary-mechanism-schema.md`
- `system/pm-intervention-summary-standard.md` — §3 Intervention Summary layout and lever tiers
- `system/brs-citation-reference-standard.md` — inline `[Author et al., Year]`; References `Author et al. (Year) — Topic`
- `system/mechanism-page-section-prose.md` — sections must not restate title, entity ID, BRS name/number, or Definition; each section follows only its schema role.

Structure:
- Follow `system/primary-mechanism-schema.md` **Section Order** (Profile A extended vs Profile A′ / Profile B). Extended profile = **## 3. Intervention Summary** per `system/pm-intervention-summary-standard.md`. **Author §7 and §8 before §3:** Foundational levers distil §7; Supporting/Complementary reflect evidenced §8 Lifestyle Levers (same phrasing, `(Evidence:<tier>)`, and citation). Every §8 bullet must carry evidence. Omit empty Supporting/Complementary `<details>`. **No** Evidence Basis or References subsections in §3. **No** standalone `## N. Timing Specific` section.
- `timing_specific` (`Yes` | `No`) is **required in front matter** on every PM page. It is ontology metadata for traversal, filtering, and scoring — not a public Yes/No body section.
- Where timing materially alters interpretation, discuss this naturally within **Functional Role**, **Mechanistic Basis**, **Lifestyle Levers**, or **Scoreable Inputs & Modulation Signals**.
- The in-body mechanism title line (e.g. `BRS6-FM1-PM1 - …`) must use markdown `##` so it matches numbered section headings; do not use `#` or `###` for that line.
- **Mechanistic Basis (canonical):** `### Summary` (always visible) → `<details>` containing all `####` blocks (primary mechanism → boundaries → integration) → optional `### 4.1 Evidence Highlights` subsection. Reference: BRS1-FM1-PM1. §4.1 is **not** inside the mechanism dropdown.
- **§4 citations:** keep inline `[Author et al., Year]` on evidence-backed claims in primary mechanism blocks; do not strip refs when shortening. Every inline citation must have a matching References entry. See `system/brs-citation-reference-standard.md`.
- **§4.1 Evidence Highlights (optional):** `### 4.1 Evidence Highlights` as a **subsection of §4** after the mechanism `<details>` (never inside that dropdown). Use `#### Introduction/Summary` (visible) + evidence `<details>` dropdown. Findings only — not mechanism repeat. See `system/primary-mechanism-schema.md` (**PM §4.1 — Evidence Highlights**) and **PM section roles** in `system/mechanism-page-section-prose.md`.
- **Non-repetition:** §1 = what; §4 = how; §4.1 = how we know. Do not restate the same claim across all three (reference: BRS1 PM2).
- **§6 BRS Pathways and Connections** — `## 6. BRS Pathways and Connections`; `### 6.1` BRS Pathways; `### 6.2` Connected BRS Mechanisms; `### 6.3` Connected Primary Mechanisms. **No cofactors, KCs, or dietary levers in §6.**
- **§7 Dietary Levers** — `### 7.1` Direct Dietary Levers (substance ← 2–3 food examples per `system/substance-food-mapping-format.md`; no legacy Diet `<details>` wrapper; no `food → substance` bullets); `### 7.2` Cofactors and Supporting Inputs (from front matter `cofactors`); `### 7.3` KCs (Key Constraints).
- **§8 Lifestyle Levers** — separate numbered section; body uses `<details>` / `<summary><strong>Lifestyle</strong></summary>`.
- Do not add body sections after **References**. No **Missing Entities** section on the PM page.

Field interpretation:
- Dependencies must be interpreted as:
  - KCs (substrates/precursors only)
  - Optional BRSX modifiers
  - PMs must not reference other PMs as dependencies
- Cofactors must be interpreted as:
  - Cofactors only
- FM ownership must be interpreted as:
  - Exactly one FM ownership
- Intervention dominance must be interpreted as:
  - Intervention dominance (inherit from FM unless justified)
- `intervention_breakdown` and `timing_specific` must be present in front matter when using the extended profile; validate with `npm run mechanisms:validate`.
- Mechanistic Basis must be complete (not missing/placeholder) unless `mechanistic_authoring_required: true` is set in front matter to defer authoring.

Mechanism rules:
- PM must map to exactly one FM
- PM must not be duplicated across FMs
- PMs must not reference other PMs as dependencies

Inputs:
- Must be derived from:
  - KCs
  - known substances
- Must not include generic dietary advice

Dose:
- Prefer `dose_sensitivity` and related fields in **front matter** / ingestion metadata for PM rows; the public PM MDX body does not include a Mechanism Summary Table or dose tables unless the schema is explicitly extended again.
- Must not present doses as prescriptions in any narrative.

Constraints:
- Must not introduce new PMs, FMs, or KCs
- Must not include scoring logic
- PM pages define core mechanism biology; interpretive overlays belong on SM pages (`docs/biological-targets/**/sm/`) per `system/specific-mechanism-schema.md`
- Must not list foods unless mechanistically justified

Substances & Foods:
- Must exist in the system
- If missing, flag:
  "Missing system entity: [name]"

References:
- Inline: `[Author et al., Year]` per `system/brs-citation-reference-standard.md`
- References section: `[Author et al. (Year) — Short Descriptive Study Topic](/docs/papers/BRAIN-Diet-References#citationKey)`
- Verify citationKey exists in `static/bibtex/BRAIN-diet.bib`

If ambiguity exists, stop and ask.
